1
00:01:57,280 --> 00:02:01,200
- Walk the wall on the left!
- I need a line!

2
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:12,440
I found her!
I found her!

3
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:14,360
I need some help
down here!

4
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:19,360
I need it now!

5
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,440
Anybody hear me?

6
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:25,280
Get down here now!

7
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,200
Come on!

8
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:34,600
Shepherd! Burr!

9
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:37,240
I got her! I can't move!

10
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:40,480
Come down here now!

11
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:44,480
Hold on.
They'll be here.

12
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:47,040
Move!

13
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:51,200
- I heard a voice.
- Help me!

14
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,840
I can't breathe!

15
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:59,560
Help me! Help me out!
Help me out!

16
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:02,680
Help me move it!

17
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,720
Bring up the skycam.
Pan it left.

18
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,120
Show me what God sees.

19
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:39,280
Okay, camera two, show me the stands.

20
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,600
- Three, give me the ice.
- Okay, graphic is up.

21
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,560
Uh, put game seven on preset.

22
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:46,000
How many technicians
are gonna be inside the arena?

23
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,320
We got 12 cameramen,
6 support... that's 18.

24
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,280
I want to limit their access.

25
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:52,640
Technicians and announcers
are the only ones cleared.

26
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,920
Hey, Spota, let us in.

27
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:58,320
Work don't stop just 'cause the
Vice President's coming, you know, babe.

28
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,240
Must be Republicans.

29
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,640
Having everybody check in through one
gate like this is a pain in the butt.

30
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:05,040
- It's only one night.
- It's the last game of the Stanley Cup.

31
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:07,560
Having the Vice President
here turns a headache into a concussion.

32
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:11,160
- I didn't vote for this guy.
- That's what makes what you're
doin' such a special gesture.

33
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,040
Hello, Pittsburgh.

34
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:26,880
Here we are in the seventh game of the
Stanley Cup finals. Penguins and Hawks.

35
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:30,600
Penguins in a come-from-behind
victory to shut down the Hawks.

36
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:34,120
Shit.

37
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,760
Sorry. Uh, my dog's missing.

38
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,720
We're out looking for him.

39
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,120
- Is it bad?
- What? You think this might be good?

40
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,280
- Let me see your license.
- Oh, sure.

41
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,560
Move. Move.

42
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,000
We are going to steal your car.

43
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:54,720
Don't get killed over it, huh?

44
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:24,160
It's the last game.
We got a couple of minutes to go.

45
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,840
Just 15 seconds to go!

46
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:28,600
He skates up to center.
He knocks down one defender.

47
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:31,840
He's skating like a madman around
the ice. He gets to the blue line.

48
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:34,840
He shoots. Whoa!
And he scores! Whoo!

49
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:38,440
- Scratch my back with a hacksaw...
- Yes!

50
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,480
Dad!

51
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,040
Hey!

52
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,360
- That's a fancy new stick.
- Michael gave it to me.

53
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:48,640
- Hi.
- How are you, Darren?

54
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,720
Darren, what are you
doing here?

55
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:53,760
- You can't stay.
We're getting ready to leave.
- It's his birthday.

56
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:56,040
And you've got him
all day tomorrow.

57
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:59,080
I just got these.
I thought the kids might wanna...

58
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:02,080
We're all going out
to dinner.

59
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:06,280
- Looks like those are Penguin tickets.
- They are.

60
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:09,120
It's the seventh game.

61
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,200
- Vice President's gonna be there.
- Daddy! Daddy!

62
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,920
- Hey, that's my hat!
- I can wear it. Mom said I could.

63
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,840
I did?

64
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,120
You know what that means?

65
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,080
- Not a clue.
- It means "I love you."

66
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,960
I love you too.

67
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:33,160
She's practicing to be deaf,
but that's still my hat!

68
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:37,320
- I'll get you a new one.
- You can't just take them
without talking to me first.

69
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,440
- Besides, you only have two tickets.
- I'm working at the arena.

70
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:43,880
- You're back to work, Dad?
- He's a fire inspector at the game.

71
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,240
- It's very important work.
- Are you a fireman again, Daddy?

72
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:50,560
Kind of, yeah.

73
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,520
Kathi tells me it's only temporary.

74
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:57,160
- He was trying to save a little
girl in a burning building...
- Are we going to the game?

75
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,520
Don't do this again. I mean it.

76
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:04,600
It's not fair to the kids... or me.

77
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,560
I promise.

78
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,720
Excuse me.

79
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:05,000
This is Andrew.
He's the head chef.

80
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:07,160
Nobody goes in that elevator,
and I mean nobody,

81
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,800
even if they have proper I.D.,
unless this man says it's okay.

82
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,000
If he doesn't know them,
they don't get in that elevator.

83
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:15,480
After you finish the Vice President's
party, this kitchen is closed.

84
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:17,600
- Have I made myself clear?
- Abundantly.

85
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,200
That's how I like it.
Abundantly.

86
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:46,240
Mrs. Ferrara?

87
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,200
Yes?

88
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:51,680
Let's just stroll into your house
like I'm your favorite nephew.

89
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:11,240
- Ackerman, Ekers.
- Yeah.

90
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:15,120
Come on, Mac. Mr. McCord makes sure
the building doesn't burn down.

91
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:18,960
Go on through, Mr. Mac.
And who's this beauty?

92
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:21,200
This is my daughter Emily
and my son Tyler.

93
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:24,680
- Want a stamp?
- Love a stamp.

94
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,920
Hey, can you guys play
after we get in?

95
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,400
Hey, hold your horses.
I'm getting a stamp here.

96
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,800
I'll never wash
this hand again.

97
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:37,000
- See you later, Mr. Mac.
- Okay.

98
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:50,560
- Joan.
- Hi, Darren.

99
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:54,080
- Are you working tonight?
- After I take Tyler to the locker room.

100
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,960
Hey, could you give Emily
a look at Icey?

101
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:00,800
Icey always loves company. Come on,
Emily, I'm gonna show you where Icey is.

102
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:04,480
Icey. Big deal.
Some fat guy in a ratty penguin suit.

103
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:08,240
That blonde you're staring at,
she's the fat guy.

104
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,560
- What's he doing?
- Shaping the blade.

105
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,880
They're like horseshoes. You get 'em
hot enough, you can bend 'em.

106
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,800
You, uh, recognize him?

107
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,680
Yeah. Luc Robitaille.

108
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:26,400
He waved at me.
You see that, Dad?

109
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,360
Luc Robitaille waved at me.

110
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,720
Come on, I'll introduce you.
He won't bite.

111
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:35,400
- Luc, this is Tyler McCord
and his father Darren.
- Hi, Tyler. How are you?

112
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,320
- Ca va?
- Bonjour.

113
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,880
Dad, what did he say?

114
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,800
He thinks, uh, they're gonna win.

115
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:50,680
Hey, that's Brad Tolliver!

116
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,960
- Dad, he doesn't have a rocking chair.
- A what?

117
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:55,840
My dad said you should be sitting in
a rocking chair instead of on the ice.

118
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:59,040
- Oh, is that so?
- You play hockey, Tyler?

119
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:01,520
No, but my dad played.
He was a goalie.

120
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:05,120
A little semi-pro in Canada.
It was a long time ago.

121
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,080
Come by some afternoon.

122
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,760
I'll show you the difference between
the game you played and the one I play.

123
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,360
I'll show you the difference between
the game you played and the one I play.

124
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,280
I can see the difference.

125
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,760
I got this one, man.

126
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,480
Yes.

127
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:40,280
You boys have fun?

128
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,520
Luc Robitaille talked to me,
and we saw Brad Tolliver close up.

129
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,760
Your friends are gonna
be so jealous of you.

130
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,160
- I wanna go with Icey.
- So does Tyler.

131
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:51,040
Icey has to hit the stands, guys.
I'll see you later.

132
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,960
Bye-bye.

133
00:12:57,760 --> 00:13:00,960
Andrew, this is Emily and Tyler.

134
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,080
Pleasure.

135
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:06,360
- Be right back.
- Come. I want to show you something.

136
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,600
Whoa! Cool!

137
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:16,240
That's why you won't hear
anyone complain about my cooking.

138
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:18,880
- At least not to my face.
- You got a burnt-out light bulb.

139
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:22,040
Could you change it?
I've got my hands full.

140
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,960
Sure.

141
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:27,520
Is that what Daddy does,
change light bulbs?

142
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,680
No, Emily.
He's just helping out.

143
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:34,080
- Firemen don't do that kind of stuff.
- What kind of stuff?

144
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:36,920
- Uh, nothing.
- When are we gonna sit down?

145
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,720
Frequent Flyer is in and on
his way to the locker room.

146
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,640
Keep him moving.

147
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:18,240
The Penguin fans are anxious
to see for the first time...

148
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:22,040
- the Penguins kicking the Stanley Cup...
- Do you have any cookies?

149
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:25,280
You force your way in here with a gun,
and now I have to feed you?

150
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,640
You don't have to.
But I still have the gun.

151
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,080
I think I have some Fig Newtons.

152
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:41,600
Hey! Caution.

153
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:43,720
Caution keeps you safe.

154
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:57,440
I keep my machine gun
in with the produce.

155
00:14:57,520 --> 00:15:00,040
Okay, Veep's comin' in.
Let's get decent!

156
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:02,080
Christ, Jefferson,
it's a locker room.

157
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,280
Duckerman, why don't you
put on a jock?

158
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:07,920
- Got any tape?
- You're covering the right head.

159
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,320
Let's go, let's go.

160
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:14,480
All right, guys, I'm privileged to
introduce Vice President Daniel Bender.

161
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:18,040
He's a big hockey fan
and he'd like to say a few words.

162
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:20,960
"A few words."
There's an optimist.

163
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,680
I want to wish you all
the best of luck and, uh,

164
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:25,880
are you Democrats
or Republicans?

165
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:28,080
Neither, sir. Canadians.

166
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:31,160
Well, in that case, good luck...

167
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:34,040
and I hope to toast
your championship after the game.

168
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:37,080
Sir, are you going to say the
same thing to the Blackhawks?

169
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,920
Of course.
Nice outfit, Duckerman.

170
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:53,440
Two nights ago with the Blackhawks
on the brink of elimination...

171
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:56,160
It's time!

172
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:58,880
I want you to pick up the phone...

173
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:03,800
and dial 555-1793.

174
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,880
- That's my husband's work number.
- It certainly is.

175
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:11,480
When you get him on the line,

176
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:15,400
- say only what's written on this.
- Ohh.

177
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:21,480
Kitchen. Yeah. Hold on.

178
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,400
Andrew, it's your wife.

179
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,040
- Hello?
- Andy, it...

180
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:36,800
We have your wife.
Follow her instructions.

181
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:44,520
They will not hurt me...

182
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,440
if you do as they say.

183
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:51,160
If you give any indication something
is wrong, they will... kill me.

184
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:59,720
When you go to the...
Vice President's box,

185
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:03,400
you will take two new
assistants with you...

186
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,560
escorted by
two security men.

187
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:09,160
Get them into the box.
That's all you need to do.

188
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:11,560
That's all you need to know.

189
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:14,280
Who are these men?
How will I know them?

190
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:17,160
In 30 seconds, you'll know.

191
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:19,640
I swear this.
If you hurt my wife, I'll...

192
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:23,000
You'll what?
Burn my toast?

193
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,360
- Mr. Ferrara?
- Yes?

194
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,960
Are these men yours?

195
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:45,560
Yes. They're mine.

196
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:53,720
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

197
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:58,760
The National Hockey League presents
game seven of the Stanley Cup finals.

198
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:03,400
The Chicago Blackhawks
and the Pittsburgh Penguins.

199
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:08,480
As we get ready for the seventh and
final game of the Stanley Cup finals,

200
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:11,920
you can feel the electricity in the air;
it sends a chill up your spine, Paul.

201
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,640
One of these clubs is going to
skate with Lord Stanley's cup
here at Civic Arena Ice tonight.

202
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,840
Listen to the crowd, Mike.
They're going crazy.

203
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:23,200
Well, here's to a great game.

204
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:27,880
Great if we win;
not so great if we lose.

205
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,520
We are ready.

206
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,600
Thank you, everybody.
You may leave now.

207
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,560
Mr. Ferrara will close up
your stations.

208
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:00,040
...singing of our National Anthem.

209
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:05,880
Oh, say, can you see

210
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:10,080
# By the dawn's
early light

211
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:14,200
# What so proudly we hailed

212
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:18,360
# At the twilight's
last gleaming

213
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,920
- # Whose broad stripes
- What the hell are you...

214
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:23,480
# And bright stars

215
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:28,000
# Through the perilous fight

216
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:32,680
# O'er the ramparts
we watched

217
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:37,480
# Were so gallantly streaming

218
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:41,760
# And the rockets'
red glare

219
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:46,960
# The bombs bursting in air

220
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:51,640
# Gave proof
through the night

221
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:57,080
# That our flag
was still there

222
00:19:57,120 --> 00:20:00,000
- I love that part.
- # Oh, say does that

223
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:02,560
- # Star-spangled
- Well, gotta go.

224
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:08,920
# Banner yet wave

225
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:12,720
# O'er the land

226
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:15,680
# Of the free

227
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:18,280
# And the home

228
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:22,680
# Of the brave

229
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:34,240
This place is going crazy right now.

230
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:38,080
You could not beg, borrow or
steal a ticket before the game tonight.

231
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:40,120
If you were packing heat,
you couldn't get in here.

232
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:42,680
Eddie Belfour
starts in goal for Chicago.

233
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:44,680
Amazingly, Brad Tolliver will play...

234
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:47,840
even though he could hardly walk today
much less skate with a fever of 104.

235
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:50,440
And here we go.
Game seven of the Stanley Cup finals.

236
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,080
And the Chicago Blackhawks
control the opening face-off.

237
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:56,440
They'll work into Pittsburgh territory,
putting pressure on the Penguins early.

238
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:58,560
Graham, slap shot!
Tolliver makes the save.

239
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:04,360
Please, he needs a doctor.

240
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:06,520
No!

241
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:09,440
Not any more. Go ahead.

242
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:11,680
